  "text": "In the short incubation period model (ME7/SincST/ i.c.), spleen PrP sc was detected 2 to 3 weeks after the titre is reported to start increasing, but in brain PrP s~ was found before infectivity was measurable in crosscomparison with previous infectivity studies . By changing the mouse genotype to Sinc pT, PrP sc detection in the LRS was delayed for a further 60 days. The timing in Sinc ~7p7 heterozygotes was intermediate to those of the two parental genotypes. This order is identical to that of their incubation period order, and may reflect not only the 1 month delay in the initiation of replication, but also the slower replication rate in the Sinc p7 as compared with the Sinc ~7 genotype [CITATION_1] . Sinc is responsible for the major rate-limiting steps in murine scrapie pathogenesis; this work suggests it also determines when the abnormal processing of PrP c leads to PrP s~ accumulation both intra-and extra-neurally.",
